(16, 1, 3, 1, 'January', 'March', 'DST-V3I1P101', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/DST-V3I1P101', 'Comparative Data Analysis on Fetal Health Using Machine Learning', 1, 10, '[\"Arosocohi Yosua Daeli, Dewi Agushinta R, Emirul Bahar, Sri Hayuningsih\"]', 'This research aims to find a machine learning classification algorithm to classify fetal health decisions using existing features of fetal health. The classification algorithms compared are support vector machine, logistic regression, and Random Forest Classifier. After hyperparameter tuning, the results obtained from this research are that the first support vector machine model obtained an accuracy of 0.88, a precision of 0.80, a recall of 0.76, and an f-1 score of 0.78. The second model is logistic regression, which gets an accuracy of 0.87, precision of 0.80, recall of 0.69, and f-1 score of 0.73. The third model is a Random Forest Classifier, which gets an accuracy of 0.94, precision of 0.91, recall of 0.88, and f-1 score of 0.89. Of these three algorithms, random forest is the best algorithm for detecting fetal health.', '[\"Classification, Fetal health, Logistic Regression, Machine Learning, Random Forest Classifier, Support Vector Classifier.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] Ying Dong, and Jia-Lin Yu, “An Overview of Morbidity, Mortality and Long-Term Outcome of Late Preterm Birth,” <em>World Journal of Pediatrics</em>, vol. 7, pp. 199-204, 2011. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/s12519-011-0290-8\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=An+overview+of+morbidity%2C+mortality+and+long-term+outcome+of+late+preterm+birth&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12519-011-0290-8\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[2] Jonathan Bearak et al., “Unintended Pregnancy and Abortion by Income, Region, and the Legal Status of Abortion: Estimates from A Comprehensive Model for 1990-2019,” <em>The Lancet Global Health</em>, vol. 8, no. 9, pp. e1152-e1161, 2020. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/S2214-109X(20)30315-6\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Unintended+pregnancy+and+abortion+by+income%2C+region%2C+and+the+legal+status+of+abortion%3A+estimates+from+a+comprehensive+model+for+1990-2019&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lango/article/PIIS2214-109X(20)30315-6/fulltext\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[3] Mary E. Coussons-Read, “Effects of Prenatal Stress on Pregnancy and Human Development: Mechanisms and Pathways,” <em>Obstetric Medicine</em>, vol. 6, no. 2, pp. 52-57, 2013. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1177/1753495x12473751\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Effects+of+prenatal+stress+on+pregnancy+and+human+development%3A+mechanisms+and+pathways&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/1753495x12473751\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[4] Terence H. Hull, Sarsanto W. Sarwono, and Ninuk Widyantoro, “Induced Abortion i