(46, 2, 6, 20, 'April', 'June', 'LLL-V2I2P101', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/LLL-V2I2P101', 'Text Interpretation in Advertising Communication: A Semiotic Approach', 1, 10, '[\"Aziza Arslonovna Muminova\"]', 'Advertising, a phenomenon of contemporary society, is information that affects the mass consciousness. Social advertising promotes awareness about existing pressing issues facing society and acts as an educational tool. Previous studies that have investigated the structural analysis of the text in advertising have pointed out that most advertising headlines are composed of simple sentences. However, few studies have explored the effect of textual semiotics in advertising on consumers. This study aimed to examine the semiotic system in advertising texts and analyze the impact of advertising on the consciousness of people. It conducted a comprehensive analysis of various types of texts in advertisements. Findings revealed that the advertising text must avoid an explicit order, encourage consumers, and not provide any instructions. Furthermore, the headline must be a simple sentence structure that can be easily understood. It is suggested that a categorical imperative must be avoided, as “softer” forms of inducement are preferable to attract consumers. The study findings contribute to the literature on advertising communication and have important implications for advertising and marketing professionals to promote consumer purchase behavior.', '[\"Advertising text, Inducement category, Text interpretation, Advertisements, Advertising communication, Textual semiotics.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] M.A. Abdurazzakov, “<em>Semantic structure of the statement (Semantic Types of Subjects and Predicates)</em>,” Unpublished Doctoral Dissertation, Ph.D. Abstract, 1985. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Semantic+structure+of+the+statement+%28Semantic+types+of+subjects+and+predicates%29&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[2]&nbsp;M. Akhmedova, “Features of Language and Online advertising,” <em>Foreign Languages in Uzbekistan</em>, vol. 3 no. 7, 2015.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[3]&nbsp;E. Belyayeva, “<em>Modality and Pragmatic Aspects of Directive Speech Act in English</em>,” Unpublished Doctoral Dissertation, Ph.D. Abstract, 1998.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[4]&nbsp;Carl Vikner, “Emile Benveniste, Problemes de Linguistique Generale, II Gallimard,” <em>Bi-Bliotheque des Sciences Humanities</em>, Paris, 1974. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Benveniste%2C+Problemes+de+linguistique+generale+Gallimard&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5]&nbsp;T. Dobrosklonskaya, Language of Mass Media Publisher, 2008.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6]&nbsp;Tat\'iana Georgievna Dobrosklonskaya,&nbsp;<em>Media Linguistics: A Systematic Approach to Learning the Language of the Media</em>, Moscow: Flinta: Nauka Publication, 2008. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Medialingvistika%3A+sistemnyi+podkhod+k+izucheniyu+yazyka+SMI%3A+sovremennaya+angliiskaya+mediarech%27%5BMedia+linguistics%3A+a+systematic+approach+to+the+study+of+the+language+&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[7]&nbsp;Georgette Dal, “Productivité Morphologique: Définitions et Notions Connexes,” <em>Langue Francaise</em>, pp. 3-23, 2003. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=Productivit%C3%A9+morphologique:+D%C3%A9finitions+et+notions+connexes.+Langue+Francaise&amp;hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0,5\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.jstor.org/stable/41559102\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[8]&nbsp;Gustave Guillaume, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">Langage et Science du Langage</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, 2</span><sup style=\"color: black;\">nd</sup><span style=\"color: black;\"> ed., Presses de l’Universite Laval, 1969.</span> </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[</span><a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Guillaume%2C+Langage+et+Science+du+Langage.+Presses+de+l%E2%80%99Universite+Laval&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color: black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[9]&nbsp;V. Gak, “Theoretical Grammar of the French Language,” <em>Dobrosvet</em>, 1979.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[10] N. Kruvko, “The Linguistic and Pragmatic Characteristics of the French Advertising Text (Based on Printed Food Advertising),” pp. 5-12, 2010.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[11]&nbsp;L.M. Maidanova, “Essays on Practical Style: for Student Journalists,” <em>Sverdlovsk</em>, 1986. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Essays+on+practical+style%3A+For+student+journalists&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[12]&nbsp;“<em>National and Cultural Specificity of Advertising Texts (Based on Materials from the Russian and German Press)</em>,” Russian and Foreign Philosophy, Bulletin of Perm University, vol. 4, pp. 39-44, 2009.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[13]&nbsp;A.N. Shukin, “Linguodidactic Encyclopedic Dictionary: More than 2000 Units,” <em>M.: Astrel: AST: Guardian</em>, 2007. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Linguodidactic+encyclopedic+dictionary%3A+More+than+2000+units.+M.%3A+Astrel%3A+AST%3A+Guardian&amp;btnG=#d=gs_cit&amp;t=1717753642600&amp;u=%2Fscholar%3Fq%3Dinfo%3AQkknC5IJsHsJ%3Ascholar.google.com%2F%26output%3Dcite%26scirp%3D0%26hl%3Den\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[14]&nbsp;M. Terskikh., and O. Zaitseva, “Receptions of Influence in Social Advertising,” <em>Communication Research in Social Advertising</em>, vol. 3 no. 5, pp. 96-115, 2015.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[15]&nbsp;Pierre Berthon, Karen Robson, and Leyland Pitt, “The Theory and Practice of Advertising,” <em>The Journal of Advertising Research</em>, vol. 53, no. 3, pp. 244-246, 2013. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.2501/JAR-53-3-244-246\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.journalofadvertisingresearch.com/content/53/3/244\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[16]&nbsp;V. Zvegintsev, “Proposal and its Relation to Language and Speech Prosvesheniye,” 1978.</p><p><br></p>', '2024-04-09', '2024-05-10', '2024-05-31', '2024-06-12', '..\\my-app\\public\\upload\\LLL\\volume-2\\issue-2\\LLL-V2I2P101.pdf', '2025-09-25 12:53:54', '2025-09-25 12:53:54', 'unpublished'),
(47, 2, 6, 20, 'April', 'June', 'LLL-V2I2P102', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/LLL-V2I2P102', 'IAV Engineers’ Perception Towards the Use of AI Tools in their Language Learning: A Case Study', 11, 18, '[\"Messouab Imad\"]', 'The concept of education has been revolutionized by many factors, such as Artificial Intelligence (AI), cloud computing, robotics, and blended learning. These factors, especially AI tools, have significantly impacted teaching and learning.  Today, many questions have been raised by researchers, educators, parents, and students as well about the excessive use of AI tools and their conveniences (blessings) and inconveniences (curses) on students’ learning careers. These questions leave much to be investigated to fill the gap related to AI in language learning. Therefore, this research tries to focus on how AI is reshaping students’ learning processes. The study’s objectives are twofold: the first is to know how students perceive the use of AI in their learning and what factors influence their attitudes toward it. The second objective is to emphasize the ethical considerations that must be considered while utilizing AI to improve students’ academic performance, as well as how to handle these concerns effectively. A quantitative approach was adopted to analyze and interpret the results of the study. Eighty-six engineering students from the Hassan II Institute of Agronomy and Veterinary Medicine in Rabat participated in the study. The results indicated that most students are moderately familiar with AI tools, and a smaller group is highly familiar. ChatGPT is the most popular AI tool among students, and most students believe it can hurt their productivity if they use it too much. The results also bring significant contributions to students, educators, and parents as well.', '[\"Artificial Intelligence, Customized learning, Ethical considerations, Students’ perceptions, Teaching tools.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] European Union, Artificial Intelligence and Data Protection Regulations, 2019. [online]. Available: https://example.com/ai-data- protection. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">[2] Hawking. S, An Interview with BBC, PMLA/ Publications of the Modern, Language Association of America. [online]. Available: </span>https://example.com/ai-an-automated-future-the-agenda-in-full<span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[3] J. Jia, Educational Technology and Artificial Intelligence. Jilin University Press, Changchun, China</span><strong>.</strong><span style=\"color: black;\"> 2009.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">[4] Wayne Holmes</span> et al.,<span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">“Ethics of AI in Education: Towards a Community-Wide Framework,”&nbsp;</span><em style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">International Journal of Artificial Intelligence in Education</em><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">, vol. 32, pp. 504–526, 2022.</span> </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/s40593-021-00239-1\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Ethics+of+AI+in+education%3A+Towards+a+community-wide&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s40593-021-00239-1\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] <span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">House of Lords. AI Ethics and Regulations: Towards Responsible AI Development, 2018. </span>[online]. Available: https://example.com/ai-ethics-regulations.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6] Michael J. Reiss, “The Use of AI in Educati