(58, 2, 7, 24, 'April', 'June', 'LLL-V3I2P105', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/LLL-V3I2P105', 'Pragmatic Aspects of Signpost Messages in Cameroon: From the Ordinary to the Implied Meanings of the Messages', 53, 77, '[\"Wenslus Asongu\"]', 'The paper examines the pragmatic aspects of signpost messages (SPMs) in Cameroon, focusing on the implied or intended meanings and the ordinary meanings of the messages. The investigation is carried out from the perspectives of Mey’s (2001) Pragmatic Theory and Grice’s (1975) Theory of Implicature. The findings point out that SPMs are not just communicative tools in Cameroon but also reflections of sociolinguistic realities and cultural values. For instance, the authors’ intended meanings of SPMs reveal their ideological orientations and attitudinal tendencies. ', '[\"Pragmatic aspects, signpost messages, ideological orientations, attitudinal tendencies, and Cameroon \"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] Junie Armelle Djadjeu Fonteng, “<em>A Pragmatico-Linguistic and Sociolinguiatic Study of Messages Written on Taxis in the City of Yaounde</em>,” Bachelor Thesis, University of Yaounde I,<em> </em>Yaounde, 2016. [Online]. Available: https://dicames.online/jspui/bitstream/20.500.12177/4461/1/ENS_2016_mem_0396.pdf</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[2] Charles Forceville, “Educating the Eye? Kress and Van Leeuwen’s Reading Images: The Grammar of Visual Design,” <em>Language and Literature: International Journal of Stylistics</em>, vol. 8, no. 2, pp. 163-178, 1999. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1177/096394709900800204\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Forceville+Charles%2C+Educating+the+eye%3F+Kress+and+Van+Leeuwen%E2%80%99s+Reading+Images%3A+The+++++++++Grammar+of+Visual+Design+%281996%29%2C+Language+and+Literature&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/096394709900800204\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[3] David Graddol, Jenny Cheshire, and Joan Swann, <em>Describing Language</em>, 2<sup>nd</sup> ed., Buckingham: Open University&nbsp;Press, 2025. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=David+Graddol%2C+Jenny+Cheshire%2C+and+Joan+Swann%2C+Describing+Language%2C&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://coehuman.uodiyala.edu.iq/uploads/Coehuman%20library%20pdf/English%20library%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A8%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%83%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%B2%D9%8A/linguistics/Describing%20Language_0335193153.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[4] Herbert Paul Grice, “Logic and Conversation,”<em> Syntax and Semantics</em>, vol. 3, pp. 43-58, 1975. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.7551/mitpress/3080.003.0049\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Grice+H.+Paul%2C+Logic+and+Conversation.+Syntax+and+Semantics.+New+York%3A+Peter+Cole%2C+1975&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://direct.mit.edu/books/edited-volume/3937/chapter-abstract/164747/Logic-and-Conversation?redirectedFrom=fulltext\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] Kouega&nbsp;Jean Paul, “Pidgin&nbsp;Facing Death in Cameroon,”&nbsp;<em>Landscape</em>, vol. 21, pp. 11-22, 2001. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Kouega+Jean+Paul%2C+Pidgin+Facing+Death+in+Cameroon+Landscape&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6] Stephen C. Levinson, <em>Pragmatics</em>, Cambridge University Press, 1983. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1017/CBO9780511813313\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Stephen+C.+Levinson%2C+Pragmatics.+Cambridge&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/highereducation/books/pragmatics/6D0011901AE9E92CBC1F5F21D7C598C3#overview\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[7] John Lyons, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">Introduction to Theoritical Linguistics</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, Cambridge University&nbsp;Press, 1968.</span> </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1017/CBO9781139165570\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Lyons+J.%2C+Introduction+to+Theoritical+Linguistics%2C+Cambridge%3A+University+of+Cambridge+Press%2C+1968&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/introduction-to-theoretical-linguistics/A3A1B73A27BE14ADF0B9F5E9A424F6C4\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[8] Paul Nepapleh Nkamta, and</span> <span style=\"color: black;\">Themba Lancelot Ngwenya, “</span>Linguistic Inequality in Cameroon: The Case of Advertising in Douala<em>,” South Africa Journal of African Languages</em>, vol. 37, no. 2, pp. 137-147, 2017. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Nkamta+Paul+N+and+Ngwenya+L.T.%2C+Linguistic+inequality+in+Cameroon%3A+The+case+of+advertising+++++++in+Douala&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.ajol.info/index.php/sajal/article/view/163754\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[9] Jacob L. Mey, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">Pragmatics: An Introduction</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, Blackwell Publishers, UK, 1993.</span> </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[10] Charles W. Morris, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">Foundation of the Theory&nbsp;of Signs</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, International Encyclopedia of Unified Science, The University&nbsp;of Chicago Press, Chicago, vol. 1, no. 2, 1938. </span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Morris+Charles+H.%2C+Foundation+of+the+Theory+of+Signs%2C+Chicago%2C+University+of+Chicago+Press.++++++++%28Rudolf+Carnap+et+al.+%28eds.%29%2C+International+Encyclopedia+of+Unified+Science%2C+Vol.+2%2C+1938.+&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://pure.mpg.de/rest/items/item_2364493/component/file_2364492/content\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[11]&nbsp;Paul Mbangwana, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">English&nbsp;Patterns of Usage and Meaning,</em><span style=\"color: black;\"> Presses Unoiversitaires de Yaounde, 2002.</span> </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Mbangwana+Paul+Nkad%2C+English+Patterns+of+Usage+and+Meaning%2C+Yaounde%3A+Yaounde+University+Press&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[12]&nbsp;Augustin Simo Bobda, “Varying Statuses and Perceptions of English&nbsp;in Cameroon: A Diachronic and Synchronic Analysis,” <em>Online Journal for Cultural Studies</em>, no. 11, 2001. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Varying+Statuses+and+Perceptions+of+English+in+Cameroon%3A+A+Diachronic+and+Synchronic+Analysis&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.inst.at/trans/11Nr/bobda11.htm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[13]&nbsp;Aloysius Ngefac, <em>Aspects of Cameroon Englishes</em>, Cambridge Scholars Publishing, pp. 1-30, 2022.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://www.cambridgescholars.com/resources/pdfs/978-1-5275-8028-2-sample.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>Frank Robert Palmer, <em>Semantics</em>, Cambridge University&nbsp;Press, 1981. </p><p>[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Palmer+Frank.+R.%2C+Semantics.+Cambridge%3A+Cambridge+University+Press%2C+1981&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]&nbsp;</p>', '2025-03-12', '2025-0