assification of the Yoruboid Group (Yoruba, Isekiri, Igala),”</span><em style=\"color: windowtext;\">Journal of West African Languages</em><span style=\"color: windowtext;\">, vol. 11, no. 2, pp. 1-19, 1976. </span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=An+internal+classification+of+the+Yoruboid+group+%28Yoruba%2C+Isekiri%2C+Igala&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://journalofwestafricanlanguages.org/downloads/download/31-volume1101/131-an-internal-classification-of-the-yoruboid-group-yoruba-isekiri-igala\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] Akinkugbe Femi, “<em>A Comparative Phonology of Yoruba Dialects, Isekiri and Igala</em>,” Ph.D. Dissertation, University of Ibadan, Ibadan, 1978. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=A+comparative+phonology+of+Yoruba+dialects%2C+Isekiri+and+Igala&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6] Akinyemi O.V, “<em>A Study of the Internal Relationship within Norhern Akokoid</em>”, B.A. Thesis, University of Ibadan, 2002. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: windowtext;\">[7] Ameka Felix, “Focus Construction in Ewe and Akan: A Comparative Perspective,”</span><em style=\"color: windowtext;\"> Proceedings of the KWA Comparative Syntax Workshop MIT</em><span style=\"color: windowtext;\">, pp. 1-25, 1992. </span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Focus+construction+in+Ewe+and+Akan%3A+A+comparative+perspective%E2%80%99+in+C.+Collin+and+V.+Manfredi+%28Eds.%29+proceedings+of+the+Kwa+comparative+syntax+workshop+MIT+Wor