(67, 3, 8, 26, 'July', 'September', 'AIR-V1I1P105', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/AIR-V1I1P105', 'The Six Emotional Dimension (6DE) Model: A Multidimensional Approach to Analyzing Human Emotions and Unlocking the Potential of Emotionally Intelligent Artificial Intelligence (AI) via Large Language Models (LLM)', 44, 51, '[\"Jeremiah Ratican, James Hutson\"]', 'The rapid advancements in artificial intelligence (AI) research, particularly in training large language models (LLMs) such as OpenAI\'s ChatGPT 3.5 and 4, hold significant potential for future applications in education, healthcare, and assisted living. Emotionally intelligent AI systems can provide personalized and adaptive educational experiences, enhancing engagement and educational outcomes. In healthcare, they can offer empathetic mental health support, augmenting existing resources. In assisted living, AI companions can provide emotional support, cognitive stimulation, and monitoring services, promoting independence and safety. However, ethical considerations and privacy safeguards are crucial to ensure responsible deployment. Integrating emotionally intelligent AI in these domains has the potential to improve human experiences and well-being greatly, but continued research and responsible development are needed to leverage its benefits while addressing challenges and ensuring ethical implementation.', '[\"Brain science-inspired AI, Complex adaptive systems, Psychology-based social robotics, Conversational AI \"]', '<p>[1] Jon M. Garon, “A Practical Introduction to Generative AI, Synthetic Media, and the Messages Found in the Latest Medium,” <em>SSRN</em>, 2023.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>[<a href=\"https://dx.doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4388437\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=%5B1%5D%09Jon+Garon%2C+%E2%80%9CA+Practical+Introduction+to+Generative+AI%2C+Synthetic+Media%2C+and+the+Messages+Found+in+the+Latest+Medium%2C%E2%80%9D+&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=4388437\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[2] <span style=\"color: rgb(46, 46, 46);\">Sukhpal Singh&nbsp;Gill</span>, and Rupinder&nbsp;Kaur, “ChatGPT: Vision and Challenges,” <em>Internet of Things and Cyber-Physical Systems</em>, vol. 3, pp. 262-271, 2023.</p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.iotcps.2023.05.004\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=%5B2%5D%09Sukhpal+Singh+Gill%2C+and+Rupinder+Kaur%2C+%E2%80%9CChatGPT%3A+Vision+and+challenges%2C%E2%80%9D+Internet+of+Things+and+Cyber-Physical+Systems%2C+&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2667345223000317?via%3Dihub\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[3] <span style=\"color: black;\">A.S.&nbsp;Albahri et al., “</span>A Systematic Review of Trustworthy and Explainable Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare: Assessment of Quality, Bias Risk, and Data Fusion,” <em>Information Fusion</em>, vol. 96, pp. 156-191, 2023.</p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.inffus.2023.03.008\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=A+systematic+review+of+trustworthy+and+explainable+artificial+intelligence+in+healthcare%3A+Assessment+of+quality%2C+bias+risk%2C+and+data+fusion&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar