(71, 3, 9, 31, 'April', 'June', 'AIR-V2I2P101', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/AIR-V2I2P101', 'The Creation of Computer Mind', 1, 7, '[\"W. Stalski\"]', 'This paper reviews the fundamental principles that dictate a series of necessary design decisions and research in Artificial Intelligence (AI) development. It is proposed that the laws of bionics be used in the creation of the human mind, particularly by maintaining maximum similarity in the creation and development of an artificial brain to the state and development of the human brain during its early years. In this context, the model of the mind (brain) should be closely linked to a general model - a human model with AI in an evolving community of models. The evolution of models with AI can take place through the transfer of positive experiences from one generation of models to their descendants. The article takes a philosophical approach to the issue of creating artificial intelligence.', '[\"Model of mind, Bionics, Evolution.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] Stuart J Russell, and Peter Norvig, <em>Artificial Intelligence: A Modern Approach</em>, Pearson, 2016. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Stuart+J.+Russel+and+Peter+Norvig+%282003%29+Artificial+Intelligence&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://thuvienso.hoasen.edu.vn/handle/123456789/8967\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[2] Anirudh Gupta, Yun Wang, and Henry Markram, “Organizing Principles for a Diversity of GABAergic Interneurons and Synapses in the Neocortex,” <em>Science,</em> vol. 287, no. 5451, pp. 273-278, 2000. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1126/science.287.5451.273\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Organizing+Principles+for+a+Diversity+of+GABA+++ergic+Interneurons+and+Synapses+in+the+Neocortex&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.science.org/doi/abs/10.1126/science.287.5451.273\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[3] Wladimir Stalski, “A New Approach to Creation of an Artificial Intellect and Method of its Implementation,” <em>Journal of Artificial General Intelligence</em>, vol. 12, no. 1, pp. 87-110, 2021. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.2478/jagi-2021-0004\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=A+New+Approach+to+Creation+of+an+Artificial+Intellect+and+Method+of+its+Implementation+&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://sciendo.com/article/10.2478/jagi-2021-0004\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[4] Jean Piaget, <em>Das Weltbild des Kindes</em>, Übersetzung: Luc Bernard. Klett-Cotta, 1978. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://www.abebooks.de/9783548390017/Weltbild-Kindes-3548390013/plp\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] Stan Franklin, and Art Graesser, “A Software Agent Model of Consciousness,” <em>Consciousness Cognition</em>, vol. 8, no. 3, pp. 285-301, 1999. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1006/ccog.1999.0391\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=A+Software+Agent+Model+of++Consciousness&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1053810099903914\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6] Bernard J. Baars, and Stan Franklin, “How Conscious Experience and Working Memory Interact,” <em>Trends in Cognitive Sciences</em>, vol. 7, no. 4, 166-172, 2003. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/S1364-6613(03)00056-1\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=How+conscious+experience+and+working+memory+interact&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.cell.com/trends/cognitive-sciences/abstract/S1364-6613(03)00056-1\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[7] <span style=\"color: black;\">David J. Chalmers, </span><em style=\"color: black;\">The Conscious Mind: In Search of a Fundamental Theory</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, Oxford University &nbsp;Press, 1996. </span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=The+consciious+Mind:+InSearch+of+a+Fundamental+Theory&amp;hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0,5\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://books.google.co.in/books?hl=en&amp;lr=&amp;id=0fZZQHOfdAAC&amp;oi=fnd&amp;pg=PR11&amp;dq=The+consciious+Mind:+InSearch+of+a+Fundamental+Theory&amp;ots=qow2ahGPTP&amp;sig=8E_1kqLUKrvyOvUqW9ELaxg6PdU&amp;redir_esc=y#v=onepage&amp;q=The%20consciious%20Mind%3A%20InSearch%20of%20a%20Fundamental%20Theory&amp;f=false\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: black;\">[8] Rapoport G.H., and Gerz&nbsp;A.G., “Biological and Experienced Reason,“ </span><em style=\"color: black;\">Biological and Artificial Intelligence (Russian)</em><span style=\"color: black;\">, vol.2. Libercom, Moscova, 2010.</span></p><p><br></p>', '2024-04-17', '2024-05-15', '2024-06-07', '2024-06-29', '../my-app/public/upload/AIR/volume-2/issue-2/AIR-V2I2P101.pdf', '2025-09-25 16:17:11', '2025-09-25 16:17:11', 'published');
